remarks: Strict dominance of a finite set over a natural number is the same as dominance over its successor.  (Contributed by NM, 26-Jul-2004.) (Proof modification is discouraged.)  (New usage is discouraged.)
statement: fisucdomOLD $p |- ( ( A e. _om /\ B e. Fin ) -> ( A ~< B <-> suc A ~<_ B ) ) $.
